properties.sfomuseum:description: Flight information packet issued by United Air Lines, comprising:a. folder with illustration of aircraft on airport tarmac; tri-fold format with two pockets;b. route map, titled “Maps of the Main Line Highway”; multipage booklet;c. system route map; fold-out format;d. flight log for service on May 28, 1946, signed by Captain George Trimble; bi-fold format;e. advertisement for TWA service, included in Saturday Evening Post (may not be part of original packet); fold-out format;f. menu for dinner, featuring veal cutlet; postcard format;g. menu for dinner, featuring veal cutlet; postcard format;h. postcard with color illustration of cutaway view of Douglas DC-4;i. postcard with color photographic image of inflight Lockheed L-049 Constellation ;j. postcard with color photographic of inflight meal service.
